{{Refimprove|date=July 2009}}
'''Shatt''' is an ethnic group in [[Sudan]] located in the northern Shatt Hills southwest of [[Kadugli]] in [[South Kordofan]] State (Shatt Daman, Shatt Safia, Shatt Tebeldia) and in the Abu Hashim and Abu Sinam areas.  They refer to themselves as the Caning people. They are one of seven distinct ethnicities comprising the [[Daju people]]. They speak [[Shatt language|Shatt]], a Nilo-Saharan language. Most members of this ethnic group are Muslims. The population of the Shatt exceeds 15,000.<ref>[http://www.ethnologue.com/show_language.asp?code=shj Ethnologue: Shatt people] retrieved May 3, 2013</ref>

